Mike Leveille (born December 25, 1985) is a professional lacrosse player with the Chicago Machine of the Major League Lacrosse. He was an All-American at Syracuse University, and was awarded the Tewaaraton Trophy in 2008. Leveille was drafted in the 2008 Major League Lacrosse Collegiate draft by the New Jersey Pride, who hours later traded him to the Chicago Machine. His brother Kevin Leveille is also a member of the Chicago Machine.[1] Leveille made an immediate impact, winning Rookie of the Week honors in first week in the league. He scored two goals and assisted on two goals by his brother Kevin against the Washington Bayhawks.[2] Leveille had worked full-time as an auditor for KPMG - New York since 2008. He now currently works at NBCUniversal. Leveille was recently voted by his colleagues as one of Manhattan's most eligible bachelors. His new glasses have added a mysterious, intellectual allure that will be sure to entice the ladies.
